About Our Institute
Jamia-tun-Nabawiyyah was created to make authentic Islamic sciences universally accessible. We bridge the gap between traditional learning and modern digital platforms, offering a comprehensive and structured curriculum to a global audience.
Our Mission
Reviving Prophetic knowledge for modern seekers, ensuring it is accessible, relevant, and transformative for everyone.
Why We Were Created
To provide high-quality Islamic education that is flexible, engaging, and deeply rooted in authentic sources, overcoming geographical barriers.
A Message from Our Founder
It is with immense gratitude to Allah (SWT) that we embark on this journey of seeking sacred knowledge. Our aim is to foster a community of learners dedicated to understanding Islam through its pristine sources, in a manner that resonates with the challenges and opportunities of our contemporary world. May Allah accept our efforts.
Comprehensive Online Islamic Course
Our flagship "Jamia-tun-Nabawiyyah Online Islamic Course" is a meticulously designed 2-year programme, structured into 6 semesters, each lasting 4 months. It provides a deep and systematic understanding of core Islamic sciences.
Structured Curriculum
In-depth studies across Qur'an Tafseer, Hadith, and Fiqh.
Flexible Learning
Weekly live sessions with recorded versions for convenience.
Engaging Resources
Benefit from visual notes, charts, and infographics for enhanced comprehension.
Certified Knowledge
Receive an E-Certificate upon successful completion of the course.

Frequently Asked Questions
Do I need Arabic?
No prior Arabic knowledge is required. All content is delivered in English (UK), with Arabic terms explained.
Are recordings available?
Yes, all live sessions are recorded and made available for students to review at their convenience.
Will I get a certificate?
Upon successful completion of the course, an E-Certificate will be provided.
Is it for sisters?
Absolutely! The course is designed to be accessible and beneficial for both brothers and sisters.
